A huge group of teenagers were staying in the hotel, and kids were all over the place until late at night...flooding the lobby, elevators, and public space.	We tried to take the stairs, but there is no direct route to the lobby and ended up on a wild goose chase around the building.	Check-in was easy, though its a little funky getting to the reception area as you have to take an elevator up a floor, but not a big deal.	Free internet is available only in lobby downstairs and if you want internet in your room, you have to pay for it.